queryLines:
SELECT
  CASE
    WHEN table_type = 'VIEW' THEN 'Views'
    ELSE 'Tables'
  END AS entity,
  COUNT(*) AS count,
  'asset' as asset 
FROM system.information_schema.tables
WHERE
  (:catalog_name = 'All Catalogs' OR table_catalog = :catalog_name) AND
  (:schema_name = 'All Schemas' OR table_schema = :schema_name)

GROUP BY entity

UNION ALL

SELECT 'Volumes' AS entity, COUNT(*) AS count, 'asset' as asset 
FROM system.information_schema.volumes
WHERE
  (:catalog_name = 'All Catalogs' OR volume_catalog = :catalog_name) AND
  (:schema_name = 'All Schemas' OR volume_schema = :schema_name)

UNION ALL

SELECT 'Functions' AS entity, COUNT(*) AS count, 'asset' as asset 
FROM system.information_schema.routines
WHERE
  (:catalog_name = 'All Catalogs' OR routine_catalog = :catalog_name) AND
  (:schema_name = 'All Schemas' OR routine_schema = :schema_name);

datasets.name: 14831c9f
queryLines:
SELECT 
  CASE
    WHEN tl.source_table_full_name IS NOT NULL THEN 'Active'
    ELSE 'Inactive'
  END AS is_active,
  'tables' as tables,
  COUNT(DISTINCT ist.table_catalog, ist.table_schema, ist.table_name) as count
FROM 
  system.information_schema.tables ist
  LEFT JOIN 
    (SELECT 
       tl.source_table_full_name,
       tl.source_table_catalog,
       tl.source_table_schema,
       tl.source_table_name
     FROM 
       system.access.table_lineage tl
     WHERE 
       event_date >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 30 DAY
       AND tl.source_type IN ('TABLE', 'STREAMING_TABLE')
    ) tl
    ON 
      tl.source_table_catalog = ist.table_catalog 
      AND tl.source_table_schema = ist.table_schema 
      AND tl.source_table_name = ist.table_name
GROUP BY is_active;

datasets.name: f7dd0826
queryLines:
SELECT
    DATE_TRUNC('HOUR', event_time) AS truncated_event_time,
    COUNT(*) AS event_count,
    CASE
        WHEN target_table_full_name IS NOT NULL THEN 'Write'
        ELSE 'Read'
    END AS event_type
FROM
    system.access.table_lineage
WHERE
    event_date BETWEEN :date_range.min AND :date_range.max
    AND target_type <> 'VIEW'
    AND (:catalog = 'All Catalogs' OR :catalog IN (source_table_catalog, target_table_catalog))
    AND (:schema = 'All Schemas' OR :schema IN (source_table_schema, target_table_schema))
    AND (:table = 'All Tables' OR :table IN (source_table_name, target_table_name))
GROUP BY
    truncated_event_time,
    event_type
ORDER BY
    truncated_event_time,
    event_type;

FROM

WHERE
    event_date BETWEEN :date_range.min AND :date_range.max
    AND target_type <> 'VIEW'
    AND (:catalog = 'All Catalogs' OR :catalog IN (source_table_catalog, target_table_catalog))
    AND (:schema = 'All Schemas' OR :schema IN (source_table_schema, target_table_schema))
    AND (:table = 'All Tables' OR :table IN (source_table_name, target_table_name))
GROUP BY
    truncated_event_time,
    entity_type
ORDER BY
    truncated_event_time,
    entity_type;

datasets.name: dd9cf285
queryLines:
SELECT 
  created_by as user,
  -- One event can have both read and write, so its not sum of reads and writes
  count(*) as data_events,
  SUM(CASE WHEN (
    (:table = 'All Tables' OR :table = source_table_name) AND
    (:schema = 'All Schemas' OR :schema = source_table_schema) AND
    (:catalog = 'All Catalogs' OR :catalog = source_table_catalog)
  ) THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as read_events,
  SUM(CASE WHEN (
    (:table = 'All Tables' OR :table = target_table_name) AND
    (:schema = 'All Schemas' OR :schema = target_table_schema) AND
    (:catalog = 'All Catalogs' OR :catalog = target_table_catalog)
  ) THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as write_events
FROM
  system.access.table_lineage
WHERE 
  event_time BETWEEN :date_range.min AND :date_range.max
  AND target_type <> 'VIEW'
  AND created_by IS NOT NULL
  AND (
    -- Find reads
    (
      (:table = 'All Tables' OR :table = source_table_name) AND
      (:schema = 'All Schemas' OR :schema = source_table_schema) AND
      (:catalog = 'All Catalogs' OR :catalog = source_table_catalog)
    )
    OR
    -- Find writes
    (
      (:table = 'All Tables' OR :table = target_table_name) AND
      (:schema = 'All Schemas' OR :schema = target_table_schema) AND
      (:catalog = 'All Catalogs' OR :catalog = target_table_catalog)
    )
  )
GROUP BY created_by
ORDER BY data_events DESC
LIMIT 25;

-- Find list of schemas WITH focused_schemas ( SELECT catalog_name, schema_name FROM system.information_schema.schemata WHERE (:catalog = 'All Catalogs' OR catalog_name = :catalog) AND (:schema = 'All Schemas' OR schema_name = :schema) ) -- Looking for their activities SELECT CONCAT( '', schema_name, '
', '', catalog_name, '' ) AS name, count(*) as data_events, SUM(CASE WHEN ( (sm.schema_name = source_table_schema) AND (sm.catalog_name = source_table_catalog) ) THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as read_events, SUM(CASE WHEN ( (sm.schema_name = target_table_schema) AND (sm.catalog_name = target_table_catalog) ) THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as write_events FROM focused_schemas sm INNER JOIN system.access.table_lineage tl ON tl.target_type <> 'VIEW' AND tl.event_date BETWEEN :date_range.min AND :date_range.max AND ( -- Find reads ( (sm.schema_name = source_table_schema) AND (sm.catalog_name = source_table_catalog) ) OR -- Find writes ( (sm.schema_name = target_table_schema) AND (sm.catalog_name = target_table_catalog) ) ) GROUP BY name ORDER BY data_events DESC LIMIT 10;

-- Find list of tables WITH focused_tables ( SELECT concat(table_catalog, '.',table_schema, '.',table_name) as full_name FROM system.information_schema.tables WHERE (:catalog = 'All Catalogs' OR table_catalog = :catalog) AND (:schema = 'All Schemas' OR table_schema = :schema) AND (:table = 'All Tables' OR table_name = :table) ) -- Looking for their activities SELECT CONCAT( '', split(full_name, '\\.')[2], '
', '', split(full_name, '\\.')[0], '.', split(full_name, '\\.')[1], '' ) AS table_name, count(*) as data_events, SUM(CASE WHEN source_table_full_name=full_name THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as num_reads, SUM(CASE WHEN target_table_full_name=full_name THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as num_writes FROM focused_tables ts INNER JOIN system.access.table_lineage tl ON tl.target_type <> 'VIEW' AND tl.event_date BETWEEN :date_range.min AND :date_range.max AND ts.full_name IN (tl.source_table_full_name, tl.target_table_full_name) GROUP BY full_name ORDER BY data_events DESC LIMIT 10;

datasets.name: 00f42232
queryLines:
WITH focus_tables AS ( SELECT * FROM system.information_schema.tables WHERE (:table = 'All Tables' OR table_name = :table) AND (:schema = 'All Schemas' OR table_schema = :schema) AND (:catalog = 'All Catalogs' OR table_catalog = :catalog) ), all_reads AS ( SELECT CONCAT(ist.table_catalog, '.', ist.table_schema, '.', ist.table_name) AS full_name, COUNT(*) AS read_count FROM system.access.table_lineage lat INNER JOIN focus_tables ist ON lat.source_table_name = ist.table_name AND lat.source_table_schema = ist.table_schema AND lat.source_table_catalog = ist.table_catalog WHERE lat.source_table_name IS NOT NULL AND lat.target_type <> 'VIEW' AND lat.event_time BETWEEN :date_range.min AND :date_range.max GROUP BY CONCAT(ist.table_catalog, '.', ist.table_schema, '.', ist.table_name) ), all_writes AS ( SELECT CONCAT(ist.table_catalog, '.', ist.table_schema, '.', ist.table_name) AS full_name, COUNT(*) AS write_count FROM system.access.table_lineage lat INNER JOIN focus_tables ist ON lat.target_table_name = ist.table_name AND lat.target_table_schema = ist.table_schema AND lat.target_table_catalog = ist.table_catalog WHERE lat.target_table_name IS NOT NULL AND lat.target_type <> 'VIEW' AND lat.event_time BETWEEN :date_range.min AND :date_range.max GROUP BY CONCAT(ist.table_catalog, '.', ist.table_schema, '.', ist.table_name) ), combined AS ( SELECT COALESCE(all_reads.full_name, all_writes.full_name) AS full_name, CASE WHEN all_reads.read_count IS NOT NULL THEN all_reads.read_count ELSE 0 END AS read_count, CASE WHEN all_writes.write_count IS NOT NULL THEN all_writes.write_count ELSE 0 END AS write_count FROM all_reads FULL JOIN all_writes ON all_reads.full_name = all_writes.full_name ) SELECT CONCAT( '', table_name, '
', '', table_catalog, '.', table_schema, '' ) AS name FROM focus_tables ANTI JOIN combined ON CONCAT(focus_tables.table_catalog, '.', focus_tables.table_schema, '.', focus_tables.table_name) = combined.full_name LIMIT 25

WITH sensitive_tables ( SELECT COALESCE(cm.table_catalog, rf.table_catalog) as table_catalog, COALESCE(cm.table_schema, rf.table_schema) as table_schema, COALESCE(cm.table_name, rf.table_name) as table_name, ANY_VALUE(cm.columnMasked) AS columnMasked, ANY_VALUE(rf.rowFiltered) AS rowFiltered FROM ( SELECT table_catalog, table_schema, table_name, true as columnMasked FROM system.information_schema.column_masks ) cm FULL OUTER JOIN ( SELECT table_catalog, table_schema, table_name, true as rowFiltered FROM system.information_schema.row_filters ) rf ON cm.table_catalog = rf.table_catalog AND cm.table_schema = rf.table_schema AND cm.table_name = rf.table_name GROUP BY COALESCE(cm.table_catalog, rf.table_catalog), COALESCE(cm.table_schema, rf.table_schema), COALESCE(cm.table_name, rf.table_name) ) SELECT CONCAT( '', table_name, '
', '',table_catalog, '.', table_schema, '' ) AS full_name, ANY_VALUE(CASE WHEN columnMasked IS true THEN true ELSE false END) AS columnMasked, ANY_VALUE(CASE WHEN rowFiltered IS true THEN true ELSE false END) AS rowFiltered, ANY_VALUE(tl.reads) FROM sensitive_tables LEFT JOIN ( SELECT COUNT(*) AS reads, source_table_catalog, source_table_schema, source_table_name FROM system.access.table_lineage WHERE event_date BETWEEN :date_range.min AND :date_range.max AND target_type <> 'VIEW' GROUP BY source_table_catalog, source_table_schema, source_table_name ) tl ON table_catalog = tl.source_table_catalog AND table_schema = tl.source_table_schema AND table_name = tl.source_table_name GROUP BY table_catalog, table_schema, table_name;

datasets.name: 84c57eba
queryLines:
WITH protected_tables (
  SELECT
    COALESCE(cm.table_catalog, rf.table_catalog) as table_catalog,
    COALESCE(cm.table_schema, rf.table_schema) as table_schema,
    COALESCE(cm.table_name, rf.table_name) as table_name,
    ANY_VALUE(cm.columnMasked) AS columnMasked,
    ANY_VALUE(rf.rowFiltered) AS rowFiltered
  FROM (
    SELECT table_catalog, table_schema, table_name,
    true as columnMasked 
    FROM system.information_schema.column_masks 
  ) cm
  FULL OUTER JOIN (
    SELECT table_catalog, table_schema, table_name,
    true as rowFiltered
    FROM system.information_schema.row_filters
  ) rf
  ON cm.table_catalog = rf.table_catalog AND cm.table_schema = rf.table_schema AND cm.table_name = rf.table_name
  GROUP BY
    COALESCE(cm.table_catalog, rf.table_catalog),
    COALESCE(cm.table_schema, rf.table_schema),
    COALESCE(cm.table_name, rf.table_name)
)

SELECT 
  created_by as user,
  -- One event can have both read and write, so its not sum of reads and writes
  count(*) as data_events,
  SUM(CASE WHEN (
    (pt.table_name= source_table_name) AND
    (pt.table_schema = source_table_schema) AND
    (pt.table_catalog = source_table_catalog)
  ) THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as read_events,
  SUM(CASE WHEN (
    (pt.table_name = target_table_name) AND
    (pt.table_schema = target_table_schema) AND
    (pt.table_catalog = target_table_catalog)
  ) THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as write_events
FROM
  system.access.table_lineage
INNER JOIN protected_tables pt
WHERE 
  event_time BETWEEN :date_range.min AND :date_range.max
  AND target_type <> 'VIEW'
  AND created_by IS NOT NULL
  AND (
    -- Find reads
    (
      (pt.table_name= source_table_name) AND
      (pt.table_schema = source_table_schema) AND
      (pt.table_catalog = source_table_catalog)
    )
    OR
    -- Find writes
    (
      (pt.table_name= target_table_name) AND
      (pt.table_schema = target_table_schema) AND
      (pt.table_catalog = target_table_catalog)
    )
  )
GROUP BY created_by
ORDER BY data_events DESC
LIMIT 25;

-- Create a temporary function to determine the full_name based on direction CREATE TEMP FUNCTION get_full_name(direction STRING, source_tb STRING, target_tb STRING) RETURNS STRING RETURN CASE WHEN direction = 'Upstream' THEN source_tb WHEN direction = 'Downstream' THEN target_tb ELSE NULL END; -- LEVEL ONE -- WITH level_1_results AS ( SELECT get_full_name(:direction, source_table_full_name, target_table_full_name) as full_name, entity_type, entity_id, count(*) as count FROM system.access.table_lineage WHERE event_date >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 90 DAY AND ( (:direction = 'Upstream' AND target_table_full_name = concat(:catalog,'.',:schema,'.',:table)) OR (:direction = 'Downstream' AND source_table_full_name = concat(:catalog,'.',:schema,'.',:table)) ) GROUP BY full_name, entity_type, entity_id ), -- LEVEL TWO -- level_2_results AS ( SELECT get_full_name(:direction, source_table_full_name, target_table_full_name) as full_name, entity_type, entity_id, count(*) as count FROM system.access.table_lineage WHERE -- If user don't select 2+ depth this query pretty much skipped to save load time array_max(:level) >= 2 AND event_date >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 90 DAY AND ( (:direction = 'Upstream' AND target_table_full_name IN (SELECT DISTINCT full_name FROM level_1_results)) OR (:direction = 'Downstream' AND source_table_full_name IN (SELECT DISTINCT full_name FROM level_1_results)) ) GROUP BY full_name, entity_type, entity_id ), -- LEVEL THREE -- level_3_results AS ( SELECT get_full_name(:direction, source_table_full_name, target_table_full_name) as full_name, entity_type, entity_id, count(*) as count FROM system.access.table_lineage WHERE -- If user don't select 3+ depth this query pretty much skipped to save load time array_max(:level) >= 3 AND event_date >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 90 DAY AND ( (:direction = 'Upstream' AND target_table_full_name IN (SELECT DISTINCT full_name FROM level_2_results)) OR (:direction = 'Downstream' AND source_table_full_name IN (SELECT DISTINCT full_name FROM level_2_results)) ) GROUP BY full_name, entity_type, entity_id ), -- LEVEL FOUR -- level_4_results AS ( SELECT get_full_name(:direction, source_table_full_name, target_table_full_name) as full_name, entity_type, entity_id, count(*) as count FROM system.access.table_lineage WHERE -- If user don't select 4+ depth this query pretty much skipped to save load time array_max(:level) >= 4 AND event_date >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 90 DAY AND ( (:direction = 'Upstream' AND target_table_full_name IN (SELECT DISTINCT full_name FROM level_3_results)) OR (:direction = 'Downstream' AND source_table_full_name IN (SELECT DISTINCT full_name FROM level_3_results)) ) GROUP BY full_name, entity_type, entity_id ), -- LEVEL FIVE -- level_5_results AS ( SELECT get_full_name(:direction, source_table_full_name, target_table_full_name) as full_name, entity_type, entity_id, count(*) as count FROM system.access.table_lineage WHERE -- If user don't select 5+ depth this query pretty much skipped to save load time array_max(:level) >= 5 AND event_date >= CURRENT_DATE() - INTERVAL 90 DAY AND ( (:direction = 'Upstream' AND target_table_full_name IN (SELECT DISTINCT full_name FROM level_4_results)) OR (:direction = 'Downstream' AND source_table_full_name IN (SELECT DISTINCT full_name FROM level_4_results)) ) GROUP BY full_name, entity_type, entity_id ), -- Union all the results from different level results AS ( SELECT *, 1 AS level FROM level_1_results UNION ALL SELECT *, 2 AS level FROM level_2_results UNION ALL SELECT *, 3 AS level FROM level_3_results UNION ALL SELECT *, 4 AS level FROM level_4_results UNION ALL SELECT *, 5 AS level FROM level_4_results ), select_filters_row AS ( SELECT CONCAT( 'No table selected', '
' 'Please select table
from the top filters' ) AS item, 'TABLE NODE' as type, '' as Lv WHERE :catalog IS NULL OR :catalog = 'All Catalogs' OR :schema IS NULL OR :schema = 'All Schemas' OR :table IS NULL OR :table = 'All Tables' UNION SELECT CONCAT( 'No table selected', '
' 'Please select table
from the top filters' ) AS item, 'NOT TABLE NODE' as type, '' as Lv WHERE :catalog IS NULL OR :catalog = 'All Catalogs' OR :schema IS NULL OR :schema = 'All Schemas' OR :table IS NULL OR :table = 'All Tables' ) SELECT * FROM select_filters_row UNION SELECT CONCAT( '', split(full_name, '\\.')[2], '
', '', split(full_name, '\\.')[0], '.', split(full_name, '\\.')[1], '' ) AS item, 'TABLE NODE' as type, concat(level, ' ', CASE WHEN :direction='Upstream' THEN '' WHEN :direction='Downstream' THEN '' ELSE NULL END) as Lv FROM results WHERE full_name IS NOT NULL AND array_contains(:level, level) UNION SELECT CONCAT( entity_type, '
', entity_id, '' ) As item, entity_type as type, concat(level, ' ', CASE WHEN :direction='Upstream' THEN '' WHEN :direction='Downstream' THEN '' ELSE NULL END) as Lv FROM results WHERE entity_id IS NOT NULL AND array_contains(:level, level);

CREATE TEMP FUNCTION getByteString(bytes LONG) RETURN CASE log(1024, bytes)::long WHEN 1 THEN CONCAT(format_number(bytes / pow(1024, 1), "#.##"), "TB") WHEN 2 THEN CONCAT(format_number(bytes / pow(1024, 2), "#.##"), "MB") WHEN 3 THEN CONCAT(format_number(bytes / pow(1024, 3), "#.##"), "GB") WHEN 4 THEN CONCAT(format_number(bytes / pow(1024, 4), "#.##"), "TB") WHEN 5 THEN CONCAT(format_number(bytes / pow(1024, 5), "#.##"), "PB") WHEN 6 THEN CONCAT(format_number(bytes / pow(1024, 6), "#.##"), "EB") WHEN 7 THEN CONCAT(format_number(bytes / pow(1024, 7), "#.##"), "ZB") ELSE CONCAT(bytes, "B") END; CREATE TEMP FUNCTION getNumericString(num DOUBLE) RETURN CASE log(1000, num)::long WHEN 2 THEN CONCAT(format_number(num / pow(1000, 2), "#.##"), "M") WHEN 3 THEN CONCAT(format_number(num / pow(1000, 3), "#.##"), "B") WHEN 4 THEN CONCAT(format_number(num / pow(1000, 4), "#.##"), "T") WHEN 5 THEN CONCAT(format_number(num / pow(1000, 5), "#.##"), "Q") WHEN 6 THEN CONCAT(format_number(num / pow(1000, 6), "#.##"), "Qi") ELSE format_number(num, "#.##") END; WITH list_prices AS ( SELECT currency_code, price_start_time, price_end_time, sku_name, coalesce(pricing.effective_list.default, pricing.default) as pricing FROM system.billing.list_prices WHERE sku_name IN ( SELECT sku_name FROM system.billing.usage WHERE billing_origin_product = "PREDICTIVE_OPTIMIZATION" ORDER BY usage_date DESC LIMIT 1 ) ), descriptions as ( SELECT "VACUUM" as operation_type, "Garbage collects deleted files to save space and cost." as description, "est saved annually" as roi_desc UNION ALL SELECT "COMPACTION" as operation_type, "Compacts small files for better query performance." as description, "files compacted" as roi_desc UNION ALL SELECT "CLUSTERING" as operation_type, "Clusters data for better file skipping." as description, "clustered" as roi_desc UNION ALL SELECT "ANALYZE" as operation_type, "Collects query optimization statistics." as description, "tables with stats" as roi_desc UNION ALL SELECT "AUTO_CLUSTERING_COLUMN_SELECTION" as operation_type, "Provides the optimal data layout and applies Liquid clustering keys when they improve performance." as description, "clustered" as roi_desc ), clusterByAutoTables as ( select distinct table_id from system.storage.predictive_optimization_operations_history where operation_type = 'AUTO_CLUSTERING_COLUMN_SELECTION' and operation_status = 'SUCCESSFUL' and operation_metrics['has_column_selection_changed'] = true ), clusterTableStatements as ( select distinct b.statement_id, a.table_id from system.storage.predictive_optimization_operations_history a join system.access.table_lineage b on a.catalog_name = b.source_table_catalog and a.schema_name = b.source_table_schema and a.table_name = b.source_table_name and a.metastore_id = b.metastore_id where operation_status = "SUCCESSFUL" AND a.operation_type = 'CLUSTERING' AND (:catalog_name = 'All Catalogs' OR catalog_name = :catalog_name) AND (:schema_name = 'All Schemas' OR schema_name = :schema_name) AND (:table_name = 'All Tables' OR table_name = :table_name) AND start_time BETWEEN :date_range.min AND :date_range.max ), clusterTablePruning as ( select a.table_id, sum(pruned_files) as filesPruned from clusterTableStatements a join system.query.history b where a.statement_id = b.statement_id and b.start_time between :date_range.min AND :date_range.max group by 1 ), predictiveOptimizationHistoryPerTable AS ( SELECT CASE when operation_type = "CLUSTERING" AND a.table_id IN (select table_id from clusterByAutoTables) then "AUTO_CLUSTERING_COLUMN_SELECTION" else operation_type end as operation_type, a.table_id, count(*) as numOperations, SUM(COALESCE(operation_metrics["number_of_compacted_files"]::long, 0)) as filesOptimized, SUM(COALESCE(operation_metrics["amount_of_data_compacted_bytes"]::long, 0)) as bytesOptimized, SUM(COALESCE(operation_metrics["number_of_deleted_files"]::long, 0)) as filesVacuumed, SUM(COALESCE(operation_metrics["amount_of_data_deleted_bytes"]::long, 0)) as bytesVacuumed, SUM(COALESCE(operation_metrics["number_of_clustered_files"]::long, 0)) as filesClustered, SUM(COALESCE(operation_metrics["amount_of_clustered_data_bytes"]::long, 0)) as bytesClustered, COALESCE(ANY_VALUE(filesPruned), 0) as filesPruned, SUM(COALESCE(operation_metrics["amount_of_data_deleted_bytes"]::long / pow(10, 9), 0) * 0.021 * 12) as annualCostSavings, SUM(IFNULL(usage_quantity, 0) * pricing) as estimatedCost, ANY_VALUE(currency_code) as currencyCode FROM (system.storage.predictive_optimization_operations_history a FULL OUTER JOIN clusterTablePruning b ON (a.table_id = b.table_id AND operation_type = "CLUSTERING")) JOIN list_prices ON start_time >= list_prices.price_start_time AND (list_prices.price_end_time IS NULL OR end_time < list_prices.price_end_time) WHERE operation_status = "SUCCESSFUL" AND (:catalog_name = 'All Catalogs' OR catalog_name = :catalog_name) AND (:schema_name = 'All Schemas' OR schema_name = :schema_name) AND (:table_name = 'All Tables' OR table_name = :table_name) AND start_time BETWEEN :date_range.min AND :date_range.max GROUP BY 1, 2 ), aggregated AS ( select operation_type, count(distinct table_id) as numTables, sum(numOperations) as numOperations, sum(filesOptimized) as filesOptimized, sum(bytesOptimized) as bytesOptimized, sum(filesVacuumed) as filesVacuumed, sum(bytesVacuumed) as bytesVacuumed, sum(filesClustered) as filesClustered, sum(bytesClustered) as bytesClustered, sum(annualCostSavings) as annualCostSavings, sum(estimatedCost) as estimatedCost, any_value(currencyCode) as currencyCode, sum(filesPruned) as filesPruned from predictiveOptimizationHistoryPerTable group by 1 ) SELECT CONCAT("", initcap(REPLACE(aggregated.operation_type, "_", " ")), "
", description) AS optimization, CASE WHEN aggregated.operation_type = "AUTO_CLUSTERING_COLUMN_SELECTION" THEN concat("", numTables, "
tables with keys applied") else concat("", getNumericString(numOperations), "
operations") END AS scope, CONCAT(getNumericString(estimatedCost), " ", currencyCode) as costing, CASE WHEN aggregated.operation_type = "VACUUM" THEN concat("", getNumericString(annualCostSavings), " USD", "
est saved annually") WHEN aggregated.operation_type = "COMPACTION" THEN concat("", getNumericString(filesOptimized), "
", roi_desc) WHEN aggregated.operation_type in ("CLUSTERING", "AUTO_CLUSTERING_COLUMN_SELECTION") THEN concat('', getNumericString(filesPruned), "
files pruned in queries") WHEN aggregated.operation_type = "ANALYZE" THEN concat("", getNumericString(numTables), "
", roi_desc) ELSE "" END AS roi1, CASE WHEN aggregated.operation_type = "VACUUM" THEN concat("", getByteString(bytesVacuumed), "
vacuumed") WHEN aggregated.operation_type = "COMPACTION" THEN concat("", getByteString(bytesOptimized), "
compacted") WHEN aggregated.operation_type in ("CLUSTERING", "AUTO_CLUSTERING_COLUMN_SELECTION") THEN concat("", getByteString(bytesClustered), "
", roi_desc) ELSE "" END AS roi2 FROM aggregated INNER JOIN descriptions on aggregated.operation_type = descriptions.operation_type ORDER BY 1 DESC;

datasets.name: 97908a17
queryLines:
WITH clusterByAutoTables as (
    select distinct table_id
    from system.storage.predictive_optimization_operations_history a
    where a.operation_type = 'AUTO_CLUSTERING_COLUMN_SELECTION' and a.operation_status = 'SUCCESSFUL' and a.operation_metrics['has_column_selection_changed'] = true
)
SELECT
    date_trunc('day', start_time) as day,
    CASE
        when operation_type = "CLUSTERING" AND table_id IN (select table_id from clusterByAutoTables) then "Auto Clustering Column Selection"
        else initcap(replace(operation_type, "_", " ")) end as operation_type,
    count(*) as numOperations
FROM system.storage.predictive_optimization_operations_history
WHERE
    operation_status = "SUCCESSFUL" AND
    (:catalog_name = 'All Catalogs' OR catalog_name = :catalog_name) AND
    (:schema_name = 'All Schemas' OR schema_name = :schema_name) AND
    (:table_name = 'All Tables' OR table_name = :table_name) AND
    start_time BETWEEN :date_range.min AND :date_range.max
GROUP BY 1, 2
